gcrypt - Modern Curve25519 Cryptographic Library
Copyright 2024 Christopher Kelley and contributors

This product includes software developed by Christopher Kelley
and the gcrypt contributors (https://github.com/CK-Technology/gcrypt).

## Acknowledgments

This software was developed with reference to the following works:

- curve25519-dalek by Isis Lovecruft and Henry de Valence
  Used as a reference implementation for mathematical correctness
  No code was directly copied; algorithms were independently implemented
  
- The Curve25519 and Ed25519 specifications by Daniel J. Bernstein
  
- IETF RFC 7748 (Elliptic Curves for Security)
  
- IETF RFC 8032 (Edwards-Curve Digital Signature Algorithm)

## Third-Party Software

This software uses the following third-party libraries:

- subtle: Constant-time cryptographic utilities
  Copyright (c) 2016-2017 Isis Lovecruft, Henry de Valence
  Licensed under BSD-3-Clause

- rand_core: Random number generation traits
  Copyright (c) 2018 The Rand Project Developers
  Licensed under MIT/Apache-2.0

- zeroize: Secure memory zeroing
  Copyright (c) 2018-2021 iqlusion
  Licensed under MIT/Apache-2.0

For complete license terms of dependencies, see their respective repositories.

## Export Notice

This software contains cryptographic functionality. The export of this
software may be restricted by applicable laws and regulations. Users are
responsible for compliance with all export control laws.

## Patent Notice

To the best of our knowledge, this software does not infringe any patents.
The Curve25519 elliptic curve and associated algorithms are believed to be
free from patent restrictions.